conversations.conversation:
			Last month, I had dinner with the Grade twelve student which is called Annie. We went to an Indian restaurant named Nakeke. It’s a restaurant located in Sanshan Street. I don’t know this restaurant before this dinner.
<br />;<br />;Annie told me that she didn’t even know where to go so she asked her classmate, and her classmate told her to bring me to this place. At about half past five, we met at the restaurant. I found that there are two more Grade ten students, but I didn’t recognize them. I thought this is such an embarrass thing…
<br />;<br />;When we sat down, the waitress gave us the menu at once. The menu looked quite beautiful and special, and I cannot stop taking photos with it. I really thought all the food looked delicious. I ordered Mix Vegetable Carrie and a pie. I was looking forward to these foods, but when I saw the real food I ordered, I felt really disappointed to those foods the food on the menu looked colorful, but the real food just had one color---- black… 
<br />;<br />;The Mix Vegetable Carrie tasted really horrible, especially the Carrie, it had a quite strange smell, and I cannot bear this at all. Maybe the Indians have different style of cooking food skills, and we are not to be used to eat this kind of food.
<br />;<br />;During this meal, I nearly didn’t eat anything. I don’t like this style of food, but I’m happy to have an experience like that.
